# Cloud Functions Environment Variables

# Gmail Configuration (for sending notifications)
GMAIL_EMAIL=your-gmail@gmail.com
GMAIL_PASSWORD=your-app-specific-password

# Admin/Dominic's email (receives notifications)
ADMIN_EMAIL=dominic@email.com

# ====================================================
# HOW TO GET GMAIL APP PASSWORD:
# ====================================================
# 1. Go to https://myaccount.google.com/
# 2. Click "Security" (left sidebar)
# 3. Enable 2-Factor Authentication if not already enabled
# 4. Scroll down and find "App passwords"
# 5. Select "Mail" and "Windows Computer" (or your device)
# 6. Google will generate a 16-character password
# 7. Copy that password (spaces don't matter)
# 8. Paste it as GMAIL_PASSWORD above
#
# NOTE: This is NOT your regular Gmail password!
# It's a special app-specific password for this application.

# ====================================================
# HOW TO SET THESE IN FIREBASE:
# ====================================================
# 1. Install Firebase CLI globally:
#    npm install -g firebase-tools
#
# 2. Login to Firebase:
#    firebase login
#
# 3. Set variables using Firebase CLI:
#    firebase functions:config:set gmail.email="your-gmail@gmail.com"
#    firebase functions:config:set gmail.password="your-app-specific-password"
#    firebase functions:config:set admin.email="dominic@email.com"
#
# 4. Deploy functions:
#    firebase deploy --only functions
#
# 5. Verify environment variables:
#    firebase functions:config:get

# ====================================================
# ALTERNATIVE: Set via Firebase Console
# ====================================================
# 1. Go to Firebase Console > Project Settings > Functions
# 2. Look for environment variable settings
# 3. Add each variable one by one
# 4. Redeploy functions after setting variables
